The paper deals with the theory of voting, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves the use of private signals and probabilistic information, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of plurality voting, which is a method of aggregating preferences that is often studied in the context of social choice theory and computational social choice (cs.DS). The paper also involves the analysis of the number of voters required to achieve a certain level of accuracy, which is a topic in statistical learning theory (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT).
